b'9. In the case of #FarmLaws too, this is happening. The very people who for decades played deceit against farmers are now campaigning on the basis of falsehood.\n\nOur govt is continuously answering the concerns and questions in the minds of the farmers\xe2\x80\x99 families.'

b'8. But in recent past we see the basis for protest is not the policy decision but doubts & rumours. False propaganda- the decision is okay but going forward somethings may happen- is spread.\nFear is being spread about what\xe2\x80\x99s not happened & that which will ever happen. #FarmLaws'

b'7. Our track record will prove the truth. 
We have brought micro irrigation to 47 lakh hectares land.

Earlier, if someone disliked any policy of the government then they would protest. This is part of democracy and it is a living tradition here, in Bharat.        #FarmLaws'

b'6. Big schemes such Loan Waivers were announced. The very same people who themselves claimed that only 15 paise of every \xe2\x82\xb91 spent reached farmers, announced such big loan waivers too. Waiver never reached the small/marginal farmers. Waiver was an excuse. It was deceit.#FarmLaws'

b'5. It is but natural, that there are doubts in the minds of some farmers. History of decades is behind this doubt. Earlier MSPs were announced but actual procurement was insignificant. MSP based procurement was only an excuse of an announcement. It was deceit. #FarmLaws'

b'4. We had promised that we\xe2\x80\x99ll stop blackmarket in urea and we\xe2\x80\x99ll ensure it\xe2\x80\x99s adequate supply. In the past 6years we ensured that there were no shortages. Even during the lockdown there were no difficulty. #FarmLaws'

b'3. Under PM-Kisan more than 10crore farmers get their entitlements directly into their bank accounts. Until now nearly \xe2\x82\xb9 1 lakh crore has already reached our farmers. For political gains, in one state, the govt there hasn\xe2\x80\x99t allowed its farmers benefit of this scheme. #FarmLaws'

b'2. b'7. Navarana 1:
May Kamalamba protect me
The Mother
Resides at heart of Kamala Nagaram (Tiruvarur)
Her lotus like face 
Praised by virtuous people
Beloved companion of Lord Sundara-Shiva
Is Beautiful 
Revels in joy out of wisdom
Like a She-parrot
At the centre of cage called Tara.'

b'4. Each of these kritis have a final verse called charanam after their pallavi & anu pallavi. Attempt here is only to give simple meaning.\nToday, we take up the pallavi of Kamalambike, the dhyana kriti. And for Kamalamba Samrakshatu, the 1st Kirtana, the pallavi & anu pallavi.'

b'3. Todi,Ananda Bhairavi, Kalyani, Sankharabharanam, Kambodi, Bhairavi, Punnagavarali, Sahana, Ghanta, Ahiri & Sri. In the Navavarna, Devi = Kamala as kritis are dedicated to Kamalamba in a temple in Tiruvarur(TN) built (?)9th CE.Shall try to explain pallavi & anupallavi each day.'

b'2. These  magnificent pieces offer a glimpse of the Tantric mode of extolling Devi. Elaborate tantric rituals are simplified into emotive yet spiritually rich songs. Kritis (songs) are structured as Dhyana(1) Kirtana (9) & Mangala (1). Each is set to an evolved raga.'

b'1. Autumnal nine days recall the glory of Devi - Sharad Navaratri. Beautiful verses such as Devi Mahatmyam/Lalita Sahasranamam/Chandi Paath describe Devi\xe2\x80\x99s qualities. These are recited.\n\nNavavarna Kritis in Sanskrit are dedications by Muthuswami Dikshitar sung Carnatic style.'

b'Long live,
Oh, pearl mine,
Oh jewel mine,
Oh my dearest eyes,
Oh mine prince dearest,
And oh my soul of soul,
These were the songs you sang to me,
But in return (for)all the above,
Oh my mother dearest
I give you but dry rice in your mouth.'

b'Neither did I give you water at the time of death,
Neither did I offer oblations to help the journey of death,
And neither did I chant the name of Rama in your ear,
Oh Mother supreme, pardon me for these lapses with compassion,
For I have arrived here late to attend to those.'

b'Oh my mother,
Crying, you shouted in pain,
During the hard labour,
\xe2\x80\x9cOh mother, Oh father,
Oh God Shiva,
Oh Lord Krishna,
Oh Lord of all, Govinda,
Oh Hari and Oh God Mukunda,\xe2\x80\x9d
But in return,
Oh my mother dearest.
I can give you but humble prostrations.'

b'Clad in a dress of a sanyasin,
You saw me to my school,
In your dream you wept,
But smothered, embraced and encouraged me, Oh mother mine,
And all the teachers and students wept with you dear,
What could I do,
Except falling at your feet,
And offering my salutations.'

b'Oh my mother,
With clenched teeth you bore the excruciating pain of delivery,
When I was born...
Shared the bed with me...made dirty by me for a year,
...nine months that you bore me,
Your body became thin...tired,
...dearest,
I can never compensate,
Even by my becoming great.'

b'During this Navratri, I hope to put out at least three verses (of \xe2\x80\x98Ya Devi...\xe2\x80\x99) daily as a little dedication, along with their simple meanings.'

b'My playlist for this period includes:\xe2\x80\x99Ya Devi\xe2\x80\x99 by Shruti Sadolikar, \xe2\x80\x98Chandi Path\xe2\x80\x99 by Shri Birendra Krishna Bhadra, and Muthuswami Dikshitar\xe2\x80\x99s Navavarna Kritis by Balamurali Krishna.'
b'Listening to the stories from Devi Mahatmyam leads us to live righteously, in harmony with the world. (All meanings paraphrased from @ArtofLiving.)'

b'Further, deep impressions \xe2\x80\x94 like strong headedness (Chanda), being unmindful/unthinking (Munda), having distorted perception (Dhumralochana), self doubt (Shumbha), doubting others (Nishumbha) \xe2\x80\x94 are all Asuras to overcome.'

b'The Devi Mahatmyam takes us through our journey to overcome the unrighteous urges within every human mind. \n\nVictory, over asuras Madhu-Kaitabha is overcoming aversion, and cravings; victory over Mahishasura is overcoming lethargy.'

b'The Devi Mahatmyam depicts the victory of the Goddess Chandi, the amalgamation of the feminine divine trinity of Durga, Lakshmi, and Saraswati, over the negative tendencies of the mind, depicted by the asuras Madhu-Kaitabha, Mahishasura, and Shumbha-Nishumbha.'

b'To that Devi Who in All Beings is Called Vishnumaya,

To that Devi Who in All Beings is Reflected as Consciousness, 

To that Devi Who in All Beings is Abiding in the Form of Intelligence,

Salutations to Her, Salutations to Her, Salutations to Her, Salutations again and again.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...reviving housing sector...growth for developers...protecting the interest of the home-buyers. RERA ...a...step in this direction...trust in the market...was in short supply due to the actions of a few black sheep, is returning...budget, announced many measures.@narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cNo growth is possible if bankers stop taking decisions on day-to-day basis. I reassure the banking fraternity that all their decisions taken in good faith with sound business rationale would not face any witch hunt.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...credit growth...revived during 1 &1/2 yrs...more is desired. I appeal to all...bankers to meaningfully pass on the benefits of low inflation to borrowers. They should...make use of significant surplus liquidity available in the system at the aggregate level. @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cToday, we have not only pulled out our public sector banks from disarray, we have also made them stronger and functional. We have provided them the growth capital \xe2\x80\x93 almost to the tune of \xe2\x82\xb93 lakh crore, we have ensured functional autonomy...\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cFive years ago, we inherited a totally broken financial system. I had an option to let the country know the state of affairs in 2014 itself...any such disclosure...would have shattered the confidence of investors who were looking at India with high hopes.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...if a business does his transactions through digital means, even with a turnover of about \xe2\x82\xb91 crore, he will pay zero income tax...availing...deductions...savings and housing loan incentives, even...with a turnover of \xe2\x82\xb91.5 crore would...pay...zero income tax.\xe2\x80\x9d@narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...GST...rate reductions, one study points out that average middle-class family saves about \xe2\x82\xb9 1,500/yr in...their household expenditure...need to encourage digital transactions...We need to inculcate habit of asking for bills while doing any purchase.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9corder to reduce litigation and ...taxpayer grievances..limits with respect to income tax cases have been increased to \xe2\x82\xb92 crore for SC,\xe2\x82\xb91 crore for HCs & \xe2\x82\xb9 50 lakh for appellate tribunals...will reduce pendency in higher courts...\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThe post of member (taxpayer services) will be activated in both the CBIC and CBDT by posting a very senior officer for this charge. They will be responsible for improving taxpayer services and will keep a watch on grievance redressal. @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI have instructed the revenue secretary to come up with measures to ensure that honest taxpayers are not harassed and those who commit minor or procedural violations are not subjected to disproportionate or excessive action.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi @cbic_india @IncomeTaxIndia'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cFor vast majority of ncome-tax payers,today refunds are credited to bank accounts automatically within weeks without ...need to go and pursue it...We are starting faceless assessment of income-tax return. This will eliminate human interface to a large extent. @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...black sheep in tax administration...misused...powers...harassed taxpayers...honest assesses...taking excessive action for minor...violations...have...taken...step...compulsorily retiring...number of tax officials...will not tolerate this type of behaviour.\xe2\x80\x9d@narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cWe remain committed to invest record amounts in urban as well as rural infrastructure, which shall lead to \xe2\x80\x98ease of living\xe2\x80\x99 as well as create more opportunities for people. \xe2\x80\x9c @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...looking to remove all delays in government payments and tax refunds so that cash-flow in the economy revives. Surplus liquidity in international financial market provides an opportunity to tap capital at lower rates...makes ...investment economically viable.\xe2\x80\x9d@narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c... issue is not merely... lowering of policy rates..., also about the cost & availability of credit...transmission...is important. We are working...with the Reserve Bank &...banking to remove blockages in...flow of credit, to small & medium enterprises.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi @minmsme'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cIdeas such as asset monetisation, asset recycling and a continued focus on strategic disinvestment are aimed at raising funds for public capital expenditure. These measures will boost growth and crowd-in private investment soon.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...budget is neither the beginning nor the end of our work in economic policy. My team and I are thinking about these issues all the time and acting on them...announced \xe2\x82\xb9 70,000 crores capital in public sector banks to boost credit growth in the economy.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...not looking to boost exports by incentives only...also to improve...competitiveness... Various measures taken...Lower interest rates, improvement in logistics sector...simplification of GST...the new automated refund system for GST will help exporters.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cvision to double farmer income by 2022 is...by a focus on increasing exports...farmers...as potential exporters...value addition...will play a big role. To strengthen this, we have already set up many mega food parks..many cold chain projects.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi @HarsimratBadal_'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...announced in...budget...to invite global companies to set up mega-manufacturing...such as semi-conductor fab...photo voltaic cells, lithium storage batteries...charging infrastructure, provide them investment-linked income-tax exemptions &indirect tax benefits. @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThis involves financial regulation, tax policy, tax administration, the behaviour of regulators, predictability of policy, quality of infrastructure...We have addressed many of these issues...and the balance of this agenda is the area that we will now focus on.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThe bulk of FDI decision-making by global companies is no longer influenced by FDI capital controls that India has, as our capital controls against FDI are gone in most sectors. Now the questions are about India as an operating environment.\xe2\x80\x9d\n@narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cVarious ministries are in continuous dialogue with different industries to enable the private sector to grow at their full potential. We are willing to go as far as needed to ensure that \xe2\x80\x98animal spirits\xe2\x80\x99 are revived and our entire private sector is bullish.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cWe have ensured clean lending and sustainable growth and I think that it is just a matter of a short time before we see the private sector booming again.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...to boost credit flow, the plan to recapitalise banks...set in motion...they are...encouraged to lend to Non-Banking Financial Companies...to improve availability of credit for...private sector...boost the economy...securing trust of the markets.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cThis depends on the domestic and international demand. We are facing some headwinds on this. One of the major reasons for domestic demand being curtailed is the credit constraints. So, it is a vicious cycle, which is at its last stage.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cIndiscriminate lending of the past created excess capacity as well as NPA problems...we have brought the NPA issue under control, there is a requirement of optimum capacity utilisation for the private sector to make fresh investment.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...the GST will soon rise to the full \xe2\x80\x98model GST\xe2\x80\x99 treatment of GST-on-imports coupled with zero-rating of exports, which is the most export-friendly indirect tax structure.\xe2\x80\x9d @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...our policies... are focused on improving our competitiveness through long-term reform measures...steps towards...ease of doing business, tax reforms with lowering of tax rates and simplifying procedures, labour sector reforms...liberalise investment climate. @narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...vision for the next five years is to have investment-led growth. We are targeting `100 lakh crore...investment in 5 years...further liberalising our FDI policy...the government will work with an open mind in consultation with all stakeholders.\xe2\x80\x9d@narendramodi'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c...past 5 yrs, India witnessed the highest average growth rate with lowest average inflation... we were able to bring crores of poor families out of (destitution)...economic growth...means wealth creation for the nation...not...more money into state exchequer...\xe2\x80\x9d@narendramodi'
